other_tests.findings: Initial ophthalmology exam showed vision 20/20 in the right eye and 20/50 in the left eye with normal intraocular pressures in both eyes. The left eye showed 2+ conjunctival injection, 2+ anterior chamber cell, and posterior synechiae. A few days later, the right eye exhibited 1+ conjunctival injection, 2+ anterior chamber cell and flare, and posterior synechiae.
other_tests.changes_over_time: At the Proctor Foundation, visual acuity was 20/20 and 20/25 in the right and left eye, respectively, with normal intraocular pressure. Anterior segment exam showed white conjunctiva and 3+ anterior chamber cell, and 1+ cell in the anterior vitreous in both eyes. At 9 months follow-up, vision was 20/20 in the right eye and 20/25 in the left eye with normal intraocular pressure. Right eye exam showed 2+ anterior chamber cell, broken posterior synechiae, a small posterior subcapsular cataract, and rare anterior vitreous cell. The left eye exam revealed 1+ anterior chamber cell, broken posterior synechiae, a small posterior subcapsular cataract, and rare anterior vitreous cell.

other_tests.findings: Fluorescein angiography (FA) revealed disc leakage and peripheral vascular leakage in both eyes.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Repeat FA at 9 months showed resolution of disc and vascular leakage.
